[[File:Invader.jpg|thumb|300px|<strong>''Aliens''</strong>'' change the very nature of the battle, moving enemies about, and manipulating the Base cards you fight for.'' - AEG]]

{{Q|Aliens love to mess with people, and they love to mess with other players even more. From bouncing minions back to players’ hands, to replacing bases in play, aliens are out to have a great time, at any planet’s expense.|[[Core Set]] rulebook}}

The '''Aliens''' are one of the 8 [[factions]] from the [[Core Set]].

Aliens abduct your friends and foes. You might see them again. Who knows?

Their complexity rating is: Low-Medium.

''Other factions from the same set: ''[[Dinosaurs]], [[Ninjas]], [[Pirates]], [[Robots]], [[Tricksters]], [[Wizards]], [[Zombies]].

== <span style="{{ColorOutline | #FFFFFF}}; color:#8F3371; margin-left: 3px">'''Cards'''</span> ==

[[File:Aliens.jpg|thumb|300px|right]]

The Aliens have the usual 10 minions and 10 actions. The total minion base power (not counting any abilities) is slightly lower than usual at only 28 or an average of 2.8 per minion compared to the usual 30 and 3.

Among their actions, there are:
* 0 play-on-minion actions,
* 1 play-on-base action: Jammed Signal,
* 9 standard actions (7 that affect one or more minions, '''in bold'''): '''Abduction''', '''Beam Up (2x)''', '''Crop Circles''', '''Disintegrator (2x)''', '''Invasion''', Probe, Terraforming,
* 0 actions that directly increase a minion's power.

=== Minions ===

1x <span id="Supreme_Overlord">'''Supreme Overlord'''</span> - power 5 - You may return a minion to its owner’s hand. <sup>[[#Questions on Supreme Overlord|FAQ]]</sup>

2x <span id="Invader">'''Invader'''</span> - power 3 - Gain 1 VP. <sup>[[#Questions on Invader|FAQ]]</sup>

<s>3x '''Scout''' - power 3 - Special: After this base is scored, you may place this minion into your hand instead of the discard pile.</s>

3x <span id="Scout">'''Scout'''</span> - power 3 - Special: After this base is scored, you may return this minion to your hand. ''(errata'd by [[Smash Up POD]])'' <sup>[[#Questions on Scout|FAQ]]</sup>

<s>4x '''Collector''' - power 2 - You may return a minion of power 3 or less on this base to its owner’s hand.</s>

<s>4x Collector - power 2 - You may return a non-Collector minion of power 3 or less on this base to its owner’s hand. ''(errata'd by [[The Bigger Geekier Box]]''</s>

4x <span id="Collector">'''Collector'''</span> - power 2 - You may return a minion of power 3 or less on this base to its owner’s hand. ''(errata'd by [[Smash Up POD]])'' <sup>[[#Questions on Collector|FAQ]]</sup>

=== Actions ===

1x <span id="Abduction">'''Abduction'''</span> - Return a minion to its owner’s hand. Play an extra minion. <sup>[[#Questions on Abduction|FAQ]]</sup>

2x <span id="Beam_Up">'''Beam Up'''</span> - Return a minion to its owner’s hand. <sup>[[#Questions on Beam Up|FAQ]]</sup>

1x <span id="Crop_Circles">'''Crop Circles'''</span> - Choose a base. Return each minion on that base to its owner’s hand. <sup>[[#Questions on Crop Circles|FAQ]]</sup>

2x <span id="Disintegrator">'''Disintegrator'''</span> - Place a minion of power 3 or less on the bottom of its owner’s deck. <sup>[[#Questions on Disintegrator|FAQ]]</sup>

1x <span id="Invasion">'''Invasion'''</span> - Move a minion to another base. <sup>[[#Questions on Invasion|FAQ]]</sup>

<s>1x '''Jammed Signal''' - Play on a base. Ongoing: All players ignore this base’s ability.</s>

1x <span id="Jammed_Signal">'''Jammed Signal'''</span> - Play on a base. Ongoing: This base's abilities are cancelled. ''(errata'd by [[Smash Up POD]])'' <sup>[[#Questions on Jammed Signal|FAQ]]</sup>

1x <span id="Probe">'''Probe'''</span> - Look at another player’s hand and choose a minion in it. That player discards that minion. <sup>[[#Questions on Probe|FAQ]]</sup>

<s>1x '''Terraforming''' - Search the base deck for a base. Swap it with a base in play (discard all actions attached to it). Shuffle the base deck. You may play an extra minion on the new base.</s>

<s>1x <span id="Terraforming">'''Terraforming'''</span> - Search the base deck for a base. Swap it with a base in play (discard all actions attached to it). All minions from the original base remain. Shuffle the base deck. You may play an extra minion on the new base. ''(errata'd by [[The Bigger Geekier Box]])''</s> <sup>[[#Questions on Terraforming|FAQ]]</sup>

1x <span id="Terraforming">'''Terraforming'''</span> - Search the base deck for a base and swap it with a base in play. You may play an extra minion there. ''(errata'd by [[Smash Up POD]])'' <sup>[[#Questions on Terraforming|FAQ]]</sup>

